canonical:
  title: 內殿春帖子
  author: 金富軾
  language: lzh
  text: 雪垠猶在三雲陛日脚初昇五鳳樓寶曆授時周太史玉巵稱壽漢諸侯
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 內殿春帖子
  author: 金富軾
  language: lzh
  text: 雪垠猶在三雲陛。日脚初昇五鳳樓。寶曆授時周太史。玉巵稱壽漢諸侯。
korean:
  title: 내전 춘첩자
  author: 김부식
  language: kor
  text: |-
    눈덩이는 아직도 세 운폐에 남았는데
    햇발은 처음 오봉루에 올랐네
    보배 역서는 때를 알리는 주나라 태사(太史)를
    옥잔에 수를 비는 한나라 제후로써
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0180&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 주나라 태사(太史) : '
    value: 천문(天文)을 맡은 태사관(太史官)이 역서(曆書)를 만들어 올려서 백성에게 시절을 알리게 한다.
english:
  title: Spring Placard for the Inner Palace
  author: Kim Bu-sik
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Snow still clings to the triple cloud-steps,
    While sunlight first climbs the Five Phoenix Tower.
    The precious calendar—like the Zhou Grand Historian
    Who measured the heavens—marks the seasons,
    And jade cups raise toasts like Han princes of old,
    Wishing long years upon the throne.
  footnotes:
    - The Zhou Grand Historian (太史) refers to the astronomical official who created the calendar and proclaimed the seasons to the people—here representing the role of measuring and marking time itself.
    - The Five Phoenix Tower (五鳳樓) is an architectural reference to imperial buildings.
    - This placard appears to celebrate the imperial calendar and seasonal renewal, with references to exemplary figures from Chinese antiquity.
